				<td colspan="2"><span>If he's triggering UDB/FakeTrak <b>every</b> single time the UDB spawns, that would be categorized as zone disruption and Guides/GMs would probably agree to get involved.  The thing is, though, for it to be disruption he'd definitely need to be doing this <b>ALL</b> the time, and it would be hard to argue that he is blocking you if you don't actually have your raid force ready to go at the time you get blocked (and subsequently launch your petition).
<br />

<br />
It's been my experience that no matter how much somebody seems to be a jerk, if you don't actually reciprocate being a jerk back to them, <b>something</b> can usually be worked out between the two parties without having to resort to petitions and such.  Just ask him a couple more times on different days.  It's likely you may catch him on a day he's feeling generous and he may let you just loot the Trak guts for free.  I think it's worth a shot to try.
<br />

